  "text": "In this paper we are going to relax the strict pairwise light-like limit which led to the Wilson loop stretched on a null polygonal contour [CITATION_1] . To simplify our consideration, we will place all operators on a two-dimensional surface R 1,1 . This is a special kinematics akin to the one discussed within the context of scattering amplitudes [CITATION_2] . The first nontrivial Wilson loop in this kinematics was an octagon. To draw analogies to the consideration at hand, we will presently address this case as well.",
